headline: Traders Search for Clues Behind Biggest S&P Reversal Since April
summary: While there was no obvious catalyst to blame for a plunge of almost 5% in the Nasdaq-100 Index from its high of the day, theories for the selloff were piling up.  The losses looked set to extend Friday, with Nasdaq 100 futures sliding 0.8% by 5:05 a.m. in New York.  To others, a strong delayed jobs report for September was the latest sign that the Federal Reserve is done cutting interest rates this year.
